The paper discusses the usability issues in security APIs, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study conducted in the paper involves collecting feedback from programmers, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). The methodology used in the study is based on cognitive dimensions questionnaire, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the issues in embedding security APIs to applications, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of a methodology in identifying usability issues, which is related to information science (cs.SI).
